==The wordy summary (because there simply has to be one).==

All religions were probably written [[over 9000]] years ago by random men with beards who were likely high on the ancient equivalent to LSD. Anyway, every random guy with beard and their followers tend to claim that their religion is the one true religion of God/Allah/The Flying Spaghetti Monster and all others are infidels, thus leading many gullible people to randomly go out and kill each other - and sometimes themselves - in order to prove that their religion is best, usually ignoring that their religion probably says that killing other people is bad and killing yourself is worse. However, this would be known as common sense, and thus does not compute with any kind of fundamentalist religious person (see [[Creationists]]).

All religions basically say, "be nice or God will get you," except in really convoluted terms (I.e, "be thou good or thy Lord God shall smite thee greatly with his almighty power"). There's usually a devil of some kind who runs hell, which is usually fiery due to lack of fire extinguishers or similar apparatus.

Despite all religions claiming to be the one true word of God/The FSM/George Lucas, none of them are on account of the aforementioned being written by beardy men on ancient LSD or it's equivalent. Thus, no one knows what actual God thinks about religion. He/she/it probably got bored when we stopped having [[Lord Of The Rings]] style wars and started playing Halo instead.

Note: if I'm wrong, see [[you]] in hell. 

